Home > Products & Applications > Austenitic Stainless Steel

Austenitic Stainless Steel
As  the most commonly used, Austenitic stainless steel is non-magnetic; and  contains both chromium and nickel, which increases corrosion resistance and  ease of fabrication. POSCO-Thainoxâs Austenitic products: Grades 301, 304,  304L, 316, 316L, 321, and 304J1, are available in 2D, 2B, and BA finishes.
[2D = Cold-Rolled Dull Finished; 2B =  Cold-Rolled Bright Finished; BA = Bright Annealed]




